<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="12Apr1939"><font color="red">12 April 1939</font> <i>NLFF</i> (from Paul L&eacute;on to Richard de la Mere): Would you kindly have the copies papercovered in the usual dummies as the copy which he has seen at Mr Gillet&apos;s does not look anything but nice. France: Mr Georges P&eacute;lorson, 60 Blvd de Courcelles, Paris XVII&deg;; Mr Armand Petitjean, 9 Chemin des Valli&egrave;res, Ville d&apos;Avray (S and O). One copy to himself for lending purposes. Switzerland: Mr Jacques Mercanton, Primerose, 1, Lausanne. &ldquo;Denmark&rdquo; M. P. Kristensen, &ldquo;Politiken&rdquo; Copenhagen, M. Fr. M&oslash;ller &ldquo;Extrabladet&rdquo; Copenhagen. Holland: Mr van der Vat ? Corfstraat 5, Alkmaar, Netherlands. &hellip; 3000 copies of the first edition. </div>
